<subSubSection id="C33C09E7FFE7FFBE675F6AB3FA22BDB4" pageId="12" pageNumber="115" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B995A6CFFE7FFBE675F6AB3FAECBDE7" blockId="12.[832,1437,911,1158]" pageId="12" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE7FFBE675F6AB3FC02BAC7" bold="true" box="[832,944,911,934]" pageId="12" pageNumber="115">Remarks:</emphasis>
This specimen possesses aedeagal characters similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2621EFFFE7FFBE60026A93FAB9BAA7" authority="Lobl, 2017" authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="2017" box="[1053,1291,943,966]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notata">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE7FFBE60026A93FB30BAA7" box="[1053,1154,943,966]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="115">S. notata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB7279DFFE7FFBE60926A93FAB9BAA7" author="Lobl I." box="[1165,1291,943,966]" pageId="12" pageNumber="115" pagination="33 - 41" refId="ref11347" refString="Lobl I. 2017. New species and records of Scaphobaeocera Csiki from New Guinea (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Scaphidiinae). Mitteilungen der Munchner entomologischen Gesellschaft 107: 33 - 41." type="journal article" year="2017">Löbl, 2017</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry id="F3311AFCFFE7FFBE61446A93FC7EBA87" name="Papua New Guinea" pageId="12" pageNumber="115">Papua New Guinea</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2621EFFFE7FFBE60166AF3FA82BA87" authority="Lobl, 2015" authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="2015" box="[1033,1328,975,999]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphobaeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lombokensis">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE7FFBE60166AF3FB19BA86" box="[1033,1195,975,999]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="115">S. lombokensis</emphasis>
Löbl, 2015
</taxonomicName>
. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2621EFFFE7FFBE679F6AD3FC54BD67" authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="2017" box="[896,998,1007,1030]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Baeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notata">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE7FFBE679F6AD3FC54BD67" box="[896,998,1007,1030]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="115">S. notata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
quite conspicuously by the uniformly light brown elytra, and from 
<taxonomicName id="4C2621EFFFE7FFBE60836D33FAF6BD46" authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="2015" box="[1180,1348,1039,1063]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Scaphobaeocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="115" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lombokensis">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE7FFBE60836D33FAF6BD46" box="[1180,1348,1039,1063]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="115">S. lombokensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the parameres nearly evenly broad in lateral view and the ventrally bent tip of the median lobe. More material is needed to assess the variability of these characters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B995A6CFFE7FFBE675F6DA2FA22BDB4" blockId="12.[832,1436,1182,1238]" pageId="12" pageNumber="115">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE7FFBE675F6DA2FC13BDD4" bold="true" box="[832,929,1182,1205]" pageId="12" pageNumber="115">Habitat:</emphasis>
Secondary/primary forest on limestone, sea level, rather dry leaf litter; understory 
<taxonomicName id="4C2621EFFFE7FFBE60C86D82FAF0BDB7" box="[1239,1346,1214,1238]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="12" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B952867EFFE7FFBE60C86D82FAF0BDB7" box="[1239,1346,1214,1238]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="115">Pandanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
palms.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
